"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-gonzaga-basketball-mark-few-on-coaching-team-usa-in-paris-olympics-it-s-the-highest-honor\", \"text\": \"In this story:  Last summer Steve Kerr, Mark Few and Team USA learned valuable lessons at the FIBA World Cup. The American team, which featured a roster of young NBA talent, went home without a medal after losing to Lithuania, Germany and Canada.  Despite boasting some of the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s greatest athletes, the stark differences between the international game and NBA game were glaring.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe all came to the conclusion that the FIBA game is way more like the college game than it is the NBA game,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dGonzaga men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketballcoach Few said. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009c[The NBA] is totally leaning toward offense \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 anything in the paint in FIBA was nothing, no fouls. So it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s very difficult sometimes to generate post-ups and post-play. There are no 3 seconds in the key defense like you have in the NBA, so there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s help side \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 in college you can just jam the lane if you want so there are not a lot of those free drives to the rack.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  For these reasons and many others, Team USA head coach Kerr of the Golden State Warriors selected Few to be on the coaching staff for the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris this summer. Few will serve as an assistant alongside Erik Spoelstra of the Miami Heat and Tyronn Lue of the Los Angeles Clippers.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhen you get asked to represent your country at the highest level of basketball, that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s as good as it gets,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Few said. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTo me, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the highest honor.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Team USA's roster will look much different this summer. LeBron James, Kevin Durant and Stephen Curry headline what some have dubbed the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cRedeem Team 2.0,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d which features 12 NBA All-Stars, four NBA MVPs and six NBA champions. The team headed to Paris boasts plenty of experience on the world stage too \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 a combined 10 Olympic gold medals and three FIBA World Cup titles.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s going to get to coach the best players in the game today,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Gonzaga assistant coach Brian Michaelson on an episode of Gonzaga Nation. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFuture hall-of-famers, some guys you could argue might be up there with the greatest players of all time. To be the only college coach associated with any U.S. Olympic team is really special.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  As Gonzaga\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s representation in the NBA continues to expand, so does the program\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s level of respect.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThere\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a healthy respect from all the guys who coach at that level. A lot of the players watch our games,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Few said.  Few discussed the honor of coaching Team USA in the Olympics, what it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s like watching his former players in the NBA and so much more on a new Gonzaga Nation episode.  WATCH THE FULL MARK FEW EPISODE BELOW:  Produced by\\u00c2Thomas Gallagher.  FOLLOW GONZAGA NATION ON SOCIAL MEDIA  Continue to follow our Gonzaga coverage on social media by liking us on\\u00c2Facebook\\u00c2\\u00a0and by following us on Instagram and Twitter\\u00c2\\u00a0@FanNationZags.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Cole Forsman is a reporter for Gonzaga Bulldogs On SI. Cole holds a degree in Journalism and Sports Management from Gonzaga University.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"